<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:5%; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="justify">The audit committee also met separately with the independent registered public accountants and the internal auditors without
management present. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:5%; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="justify">In reliance on the reviews and discussions with management and the independent registered public
accountants, the audit committee recommended to the board of directors, and the board approved, the inclusion of the audited financial statements in the annual report on Form&nbsp;10-K for the year ended December&nbsp;31, 2015 filed with the SEC.
The audit committee has also selected Ernst&nbsp;&amp; Young LLP as independent registered public accountants for 2016. The board has proposed that the stockholders ratify this selection at the annual meeting. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman">James H. Quigley, Chairman </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Rodney F. Chase </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Terrence J. Checki </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Kevin&nbsp;O. Meyers </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Fredric G. Reynolds </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman">William G. Schrader </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><I>Risk Management Oversight </I></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:5%; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="justify">In the normal course of its business, the company is exposed to a variety of risks, including market risks relating to changes
in commodity prices, interest rates and currencies, technical risks affecting the company&#146;s resource base, political and regulatory risks and credit and investment risks. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">20 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:5%; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="justify">The company operates a risk control program under the direction of its chief risk
officer and through its corporate risk policy, which senior management has approved. The company is continuing to develop and implement an enterprise risk program across the company to strengthen the consistency of risk consideration in making
business decisions. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:5%; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="justify">The audit committee of the board of directors has been delegated primary responsibility for oversight
of the company&#146;s risk management practices. At least annually, the chief risk officer presents a comprehensive review of the company&#146;s corporate risk policy to the audit committee, discussing the risk control organization and risk control
practices. The audit committee will also receive updates at other meetings during the year on any particular matters relating to risk controls that management believes needs to be brought to the attention of the committee. In addition, the full
board of directors has oversight of the company&#146;s risk management policies with an emphasis on understanding the key enterprise risks affecting the company&#146;s business and the ways in which the company attempts to prudently mitigate such
risks, to the extent reasonably practicable and consistent with the company&#146;s long-term strategies. In addition, the company conducts an annual risk assessment to determine the extent, if any, to which the company&#146;s compensation programs
and practices may create incentives for excessive risk-taking. For a discussion of this assessment, see &#147;Compensation and Risk&#148; on page 55. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">21 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3"><B><A NAME="toc96296_7"></A>Section&nbsp;16(a) Beneficial Ownership Reporting Compliance
</B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:5%" ALIGN="justify"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">Section&nbsp;16(a) of the Securities Exchange Act of 1934, as amended (the &#147;Exchange Act&#148;)
requires the company&#146;s directors, certain of its officers and persons who beneficially own more than 10% of the company&#146;s common stock to file initial reports of ownership and reports of changes in ownership with the SEC. Based solely on
the company&#146;s review of copies of such reports, and on written representations from such reporting persons, the company believes that in 2015 all such reporting persons filed the required reports on a timely basis in accordance with
Section&nbsp;16(a). </FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">22 </FONT></P>



<p Style='page-break-before:always'>

<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><B><A NAME="toc96296_8"></A>Ownership of Voting Securities by Certain Beneficial Owners </B></P>

December&nbsp;31, 2015 for Elliott Associates, L.P., The Vanguard Group and BlackRock, Inc., information as to the ownership of more than 5% of any class of the company&#146;s voting securities by beneficial owners known by the company to hold more
than 5% of any such class: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

the table. Where no information appears in the column &#147;Percent of outstanding shares of common stock owned,&#148; the securities held represent less than 1% of the common stock outstanding. </P>

<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(a)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt">These figures include 58,438 shares vested in the name of Mr.&nbsp;Hess, 4,352&nbsp;shares vested in the name of Mr.&nbsp;Rielly and
64,137&nbsp;shares vested for all executive officers and directors as a group under the employees&#146; savings plan as to which these individuals and the group have voting and dispositive power. These amounts also include 29,834&nbsp;shares held in
escrow under the second amended and restated 1995 LTI plan or the 2008 LTI plan, as amended, or both, for Mr.&nbsp;Goodell, 96,867&nbsp;shares held in escrow under these plans for Mr.&nbsp;Hess, 63,690&nbsp;shares held in escrow under these plans
for Mr.&nbsp;Hill, 29,834&nbsp;shares held in escrow under the these plans for Mr.&nbsp;Rielly, 24,380 shares held in escrow under these plans for Mr.&nbsp;Turner and 212,543&nbsp;shares held in escrow under these plans for all executive officers
and directors as a group. As to these shares, these individuals and the group have voting power but not dispositive power. Holders of stock options do not have the right to vote or any other right of a stockholder with respect to shares of common
stock underlying such options until they are exercised. These amounts also include 1,901 shares beneficially owned by Ms.&nbsp;Holiday, 218,222 shares beneficially owned by Mr.&nbsp;Hess, 21,822 shares beneficially owned by Mr.&nbsp;Golub, 4,364
shares beneficially owned by Mr.&nbsp;McManus, 1,901 shares beneficially owned by Mr.&nbsp;Meyers and 6,546 shares beneficially owned by Mr.&nbsp;Wilson, which represent shares of common stock issuable upon conversion of the company&#146;s mandatory
convertible preferred stock. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

Owners.&#148; </P></TD></TR></TABLE>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><B><A NAME="toc96296_11"></A>Executive Compensation </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B><U>Compensation Discussion and Analysis </U></B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:5%; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="justify">This Compensation Discussion and Analysis (&#147;CD&amp;A&#148;) explains the key elements of our executive compensation
program and 2015 compensation decisions for our named executive officers (&#147;NEOs&#148;). The compensation and management development committee of our board of directors (the &#147;compensation committee&#148; or the &#147;committee&#148;), with
input from its independent compensation consultant, oversees these programs and determines compensation for our NEOs. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:5%; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="justify">For
fiscal year 2015, our NEOs were: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD NOWRAP VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>Executive Summary </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:5%; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="justify"><B><I>Summary of Hess&#146; Business</I></B>.<B><I></I></B> Hess Corporation is a leading global independent energy company
engaged in the exploration and production of crude oil and natural gas. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:5%; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="justify">In 2015, the board of directors and management
team completed the process of transforming Hess from an integrated energy company into a more geographically focused pure play exploration and production (&#147;E&amp;P&#148;) company. This multi-year, strategic transformation was designed to drive
cash generative growth and sustainable returns to stockholders by leveraging our lean manufacturing capabilities, exploiting our deepwater drilling and project development capabilities and executing a smaller, more targeted exploratory program. We
have a diversified portfolio of high-quality assets, with a balanced mix between unconventional and conventional resources, located onshore and offshore in the U.S. and select locations around the world, where we believe we have a competitive
advantage. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">27 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:5%; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="justify"><B><I>Response to Low Oil Price Environment</I></B>. In response to the decline
in oil prices, in 2015 we focused on preserving the strength of our balance sheet, while maintaining our operating capabilities and preserving our long-term growth options. Through extensive cost reduction efforts, we decreased capital and
exploratory expenditures and cash operating costs by approximately $700 million, while increasing net production by 14% from 2014, to 375,000 barrels of oil equivalent per day. In addition, in July 2015, we sold a 50% interest in our Bakken
midstream assets for net cash consideration of approximately $2.6 billion. By adhering to this disciplined approach, we finished the year with one of the strongest balance sheets and liquidity positions among our E&amp;P peers, with $2.7 billion of
cash, total liquidity including available committed credit facilities of approximately $7.4 billion, and a debt-to-capitalization ratio, excluding the Bakken Midstream joint venture, of approximately 24.4%. In February 2016 we further strengthened
our balance sheet and liquidity position by raising an additional $1.6 billion through public offerings of common stock and mandatory convertible preferred stock. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:5%; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="justify"><B><I>Compensation Actions to Recognize Low Commodity Price Environment.</I></B> Given the low oil price environment, and our
disciplined approach to executive compensation, the committee approved the following compensation actions for 2015 and 2016: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:12pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:12pt">held salaries flat at 2014 levels for our NEOs during 2015 and 2016; </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:12pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:12pt">applied negative discretion to reduce the payouts to our NEOs for the enterprise performance component of the annual incentive plan from 111% to
85%, despite strong 2015 enterprise results, and made no adjustments for 2015 individual performance; </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:12pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:12pt">held flat annual incentive plan targets for our NEOs in 2015 and 2016; and </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:12pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:12pt">reduced grant date values of long-term incentive awards for each of our NEOs in 2015 compared to 2014 to reflect the low commodity price
environment and manage share utilization, and further reduced grant date values of long-term incentive awards in 2016 by an additional 15% from 2015 levels. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:5%; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="justify"><B><I>2015 Corporate Performance Overview</I></B>. 2015 was a strong operational year for Hess. Despite record low commodity
prices, we increased net production year-over-year and progressed our offshore developments to preserve long-term growth options. We also completed execution of our strategic plan to transition to a pure play E&amp;P company. The resulting smaller,
restructured organization, combined with a strong balance sheet, leaves the company better positioned in the current oil price environment. For the three-year period ending December&nbsp;31, 2015, our total shareholder return (&#147;TSR&#148;),
which is the change in stock price plus reinvested dividends, was top quartile compared to our 2015 peer companies. Select highlights are summarized in the following table. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">28 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">


<TR>
<TD WIDTH="98%"></TD></TR>


<TR BGCOLOR="#26962d" STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:9pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt; padding-right:8pt"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff"><B><FONT COLOR="#ffffff">Highlights</FONT></B></FONT></TD></TR>

<TR STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt; padding-right:8pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>Strategic Initiatives</B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;Sold a 50% interest in our Bakken midstream assets for net cash consideration of approximately $2.6
billion</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;Completed execution of strategic plan to transition to a pure play E&amp;P company</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;Completed sale of energy trading business and Hovensa LLC&#146;s (&#147;Hovensa&#148;) storage
terminals, refining units and marine infrastructure</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:2.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;Positioned the company for initial public
offering of Bakken midstream MLP</P></TD></TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#edf9d8" STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt; padding-right:8pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>Operations</B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;Total production averaged 375,000 barrels of oil equivalent (&#147;BOE&#148;) per day, compared to
329,000 BOE per day in 2014</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;Bakken production averaged 112,000 BOE per day, an increase of 35%
from 2014</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:2.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;Achieved safety improvements, through reduced safety-related HiPO incidents and lower
total recordable incident rate (TRIR) compared to 2014</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt; padding-right:8pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>Cost Reduction / Spending
Efficiency</B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;Reduced capital and exploratory expenditures by $400 million and cash operating
costs by approximately $300 million</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;Continued to drive down Bakken drilling and completion costs
per operated well to $5.8 million in 2015 and $5.1 million in the 4<SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">th</SUP> quarter of 2015, leveraging lean manufacturing practices</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:2.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;2015 E&amp;P capital and exploratory expenditures were $4.0 billion, down approximately 25% from
$5.3 billion in 2014, and planned 2016 E&amp;P capital and exploratory expenditures were reduced by another 40% to $2.4 billion.</P></TD></TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#edf9d8" STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt; padding-right:8pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>Finance</B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;$2.7 billion of cash on our balance sheet at year-end 2015 and a $4 billion committed undrawn
revolver available until 2020</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;Debt to capitalization ratio of 24.4% at year-end (excluding
Bakken midstream)</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:2.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;Improved liquidity by raising $1.6 billion through public equity offerings in
early 2016</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt; padding-right:8pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>Exploration</B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;Significant oil discovery at the Liza-1 well in Guyana during 2015, 3D seismic shoot is near
completion</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;Successful initial exploration well at the Sicily prospect in the Gulf of Mexico was
completed in 2015</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:2.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;Commenced drilling at the Melmar prospect in the Gulf of Mexico in December
2015</P></TD></TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#edf9d8" STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt; padding-right:8pt">
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>Governance</B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;Board adopted proxy access by-law permitting stockholders owning 3% of the common stock for 3 years
to include up to the greater of two director nominees or 20% of the board in the company&#146;s proxy materials</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:2.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;Board adopted a compensation clawback policy for senior executives.</P></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:5%; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="justify"><B><I>Summary of Hess&#146; 2015 Executive Compensation Program</I></B>. A
summary of our executive compensation program during 2015 is provided below. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">


<TR>
<TD WIDTH="50%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="3%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="46%"></TD></TR>


<TR BGCOLOR="#26962d" STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:9pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" COLSPAN="3" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt; padding-right:8pt"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff"><B><FONT COLOR="#ffffff">Compensation
Philosophy</FONT></B></FONT></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:9pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" COLSPAN="3" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt; padding-right:8pt">
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:'WINGDINGS 2'">&#161;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Generally, we target total direct compensation
(salary, annual incentive and long-term incentives) within a competitive range of market median.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:'WINGDINGS 2'">&#161;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Sustained performance may be recognized in
individual pay components, and pay will vary above or below target based primarily on enterprise and, to a lesser degree, individual performance outcomes.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:'WINGDINGS 2'">&#161;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Annual incentive plan emphasizes operational
elements; long-term incentives align with long-term stockholder value and reflect both our performance relative to peers and how our stock performed over a multi-year period.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:'WINGDINGS 2'">&#161;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Annual incentive plan provides greater emphasis
on formulaic enterprise results and decreased weighting on individual results.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:'WINGDINGS 2'">&#161;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Long-term incentives are delivered using
different types of awards to balance absolute and relative performance, over varying time horizons, and retention considerations.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:'WINGDINGS 2'">&#161;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Mix of long-term awards is heavily
performance-contingent (80% to 100%), based on grant date target value.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#26962d" STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:9pt">
<TD VALIGN="bottom" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff"><B><FONT COLOR="#ffffff">Compensation Element</FONT></B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; padding-right:8pt"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff"><B><FONT COLOR="#ffffff">2015 Result</FONT></B></FONT></TD></TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#edf9d8" STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>Base Salary</B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:2.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:'WINGDINGS 2'">&#161;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Fixed rate of pay</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; padding-right:8pt"><B>Base salaries held flat. No increase for NEOs.</B></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE="margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>Annual Incentive Plan (&#147;AIP&#148;)</B></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; padding-right:8pt"><B>Enterprise Result was 111% of target. In light of</B></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt">
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:'WINGDINGS 2'">&#161;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Payout from 0%-200% of target</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:'WINGDINGS 2'">&#161;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Payout based on enterprise performance factor
(0%-175% of target) and an individual performance modifier of 0% to +25% of target</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT
STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:'WINGDINGS 2'">&#161;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;2015 Enterprise performance metrics included:</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:3.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">1.
Environment, health and safety</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:3.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">2. Exploration resource additions</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:3.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">3. Production</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:3.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">4. Controllable operated cash costs</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:3.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">5. E&amp;P capital and exploratory spend</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:3.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">6. Cash return on capital employed</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; padding-right:8pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>the current commodity price environment, the committee exercised negative
discretion to reduce payouts to 85%</B></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Individual modifiers for all NEOs resulted in
no adjustment to enterprise results.</P></TD></TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#edf9d8" STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE="margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>Long-term Incentives (&#147;LTI&#148;)</B></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; padding-right:8pt"><B>Reduced grant date value of 2015 awards to reflect</B></TD></TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#edf9d8" STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT
STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:'WINGDINGS 2'">&#161;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;60% Performance Share Units (&#147;PSUs&#148;); payout from 0%-200% of target</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:'WINGDINGS 2'">&#161;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;20% Stock Options; stock price must appreciate
for any value to be realized</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:2.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:'WINGDINGS 2'">&#161;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;20% Restricted
Stock</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:8pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>current commodity price environment and to
manage share utilization.</B> </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">PSUs at-risk based on three-year TSR performance
compared to peers.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B></B>Payout of PSUs for the 2013-15 performance period was 200%
of target, given top quartile TSR performance versus peers.<B></B></P></TD></TR>
</TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">30 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:5%; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="justify"><B><I>2013 PSU Award Payout.</I></B>&nbsp;As described below under &#147;LTI
Program Structure,&#148; long-term incentive compensation is an important tool to support execution of our long-term business strategy, which is particularly important in capital-intensive industries, such as ours, and represents the largest portion
of each executive officer&#146;s target total direct compensation package. In 2013, 50% of LTI awarded to our NEOs was in the form of PSUs, for which the potential payout thresholds are pre-determined at the time of grant, depending upon the
company&#146;s TSR compared with that of our peer companies over a three-year period. The committee certified performance results with respect to the 2013 to 2015 performance period in February 2016 and determined that for this performance period,
Hess TSR was positive and ranked third among our peers, a substantial majority of which had negative TSR during this period. As a result of Hess&#146; outperformance versus our peers, including positive TSR during the relevant performance period,
200% of the target number of PSUs were earned with respect to the 2013 award and were paid in 2016. For a list of the peer companies used in the relative comparison, see our proxy statement, filed with the SEC on March&nbsp;27, 2014. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:5%; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="justify"><B><I>Pay Mix</I></B>. The majority of NEO compensation is variable. For our CEO and other NEOs, approximately 90% and 80%,
respectively, on average, of 2015 target total direct compensation was variable. Variable pay directly ties their pay to company performance outcomes, both retrospectively and prospectively, including financial results, operational results,
strategic initiatives, and stock price performance. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:5%; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="justify">In 2015,&nbsp;Mr. Hess&#146; cash bonus target was $2.25 million
reflecting a reduction from 2014 to align a greater portion of Mr.&nbsp;Hess&#146; target total direct compensation with the company&#146;s long-term performance. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt" ALIGN="center">


<IMG SRC="g96296g55h74.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
 </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:5%; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="justify"><B><I>CEO 2016 Pay Mix. </I></B>In early 2016, the committee approved certain changes to
the long-term incentive mix for Mr.&nbsp;Hess for 2016 to eliminate the restricted stock component from his long-term incentive compensation and to increase the PSU component and the stock option component of his long-term incentive compensation to
70% and 30%, respectively. As a result, 100% of Mr.&nbsp;Hess&#146; long term incentive compensation will be performance-based, further aligning Mr.&nbsp;Hess&#146; total compensation with the company&#146;s long-term performance. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">31 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:5%; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="justify"><B><I>Pay vs. Performance Alignment (Realizable Compensation)</I></B>.&nbsp;A
comparison of realizable pay to target pay, based on the grant date opportunity, and TSR illustrates how performance outcomes have impacted pay over time. The graph below shows the average realizable pay of the CEO for each of the three-year periods
ending December&nbsp;31, 2013, 2014 and 2015, and the correlation with the indexed TSR of Hess common stock. As shown below, realizable CEO compensation is sensitive to TSR, illustrating alignment with stockholder interests. </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:18pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt" ALIGN="center">


<IMG SRC="g96296g73o11.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
 </P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(1)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt">Grant date opportunity reflects the average of salary, target cash bonus, and grant date fair market value of equity awards, as reported in the
Grants of Plan-Based Awards Table, for each respective year. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(2)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt">Realizable pay reflects the average of salary, actual cash bonus, and the intrinsic value of stock options, the market value of restricted stock,
and the market value of PSUs (tracking actual performance), in each case awarded in each of these three-year periods. Stock options, restricted stock, and PSUs are valued at year end 2013, 2014 and 2015 closing prices of common stock.
</P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(3)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt">For more information on total compensation as calculated under SEC rules, see the narrative and notes accompanying the Summary Compensation Table
on page&nbsp;47. The amounts reported as realizable compensation differs substantially from the amounts reported as total compensation in the Summary Compensation Table and is not a substitute for those amounts. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">32 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B><A NAME="tx96296_101"></A>2015 Say on Pay Vote Result and Ongoing Stockholder Engagement </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:5%; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="justify">At our 2015 annual meeting of stockholders, over 96% of votes cast supported Hess&#146; executive compensation program. We view
this as an affirmation of our current pay practices. We regularly engage stockholders to discuss a variety of aspects of our business and welcome stockholder input and feedback. The &#147;say on pay&#148; vote serves as an additional tool to guide
the board and the committee in ensuring alignment of our executive compensation programs with stockholder interests. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:5%; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="justify">Specifically, we engage with our stockholders in order to ensure we fully understand the factors they consider to be the most
important when evaluating our executive compensation program. During 2015, our CEO and other members of senior management conducted a broad outreach effort which included nearly 200 meetings with institutional investors representing&#151;in the
aggregate&#151;over 50% of our outstanding shares. The purpose of this outreach was to discuss and solicit stockholder views on our strategy, business plan, corporate governance and other matters of concern, including executive compensation. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B><A NAME="tx96296_102"></A>Total Compensation &#150; Objectives, Philosophy and Key Practices </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:5%; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="justify"><B></B><B><I>Objectives</I></B><B></B>. The objective of our executive compensation program is to attract and retain talented
executives and motivate them to achieve our business goals through a combination of cash and stock-based compensation. The principal elements of an executive&#146;s total compensation consist of: <B> </B></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:12pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:12pt">base salary, </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:12pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:12pt">annual incentive, and </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:12pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="justify" STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:12pt">long-term incentives. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="justify">We also review other elements of compensation, including retirement benefits, health and welfare plans and other benefits offered to employees
generally in order to evaluate the entire compensation package offered to executives. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:5%; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="justify"><B><I>Compensation
Philosophy</I></B>. Generally, we target total direct compensation (salary, annual incentive and long-term incentives) within a competitive range of market median. Sustained performance may be recognized in individual pay components, and pay will
vary above or below target based primarily on actual enterprise performance and, to a lesser degree, individual performance. Variations in total direct compensation among the NEOs reflect differences in competitive pay for their respective positions
as well as the size and complexity of the business units or functions they oversee, the performance of those business units or functions, and individual performance. The committee also considers market conditions in our industry when making
compensation decisions. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">33 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

are summarized below. We believe these practices promote alignment with the interests of our stockholders. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1.50pt solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE="margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT COLOR="#bc0000">x</FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1.50pt solid #000000; padding-right:8pt">No excise tax gross-ups in change-in-control agreements since 2010</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:9pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1.50pt solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE="margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT COLOR="#bc0000">x</FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1.50pt solid #000000; padding-right:8pt">No re-pricing of underwater stock options without stockholder approval</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:9pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1.50pt solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1.50pt solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE="margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:9pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT COLOR="#bc0000">x</FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1.50pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1.50pt solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1.50pt solid #000000; padding-right:8pt">No excessive severance or change in control benefits</TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B><A NAME="tx96296_103"></A>2015 Total Direct Compensation </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:5%; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="justify">We structure NEO total direct compensation so that the majority is delivered in the form of equity awards, in order to provide
incentives to work toward growth of long-term profitability that will enhance stockholder returns. We also structure NEOs&#146; cash compensation so that a significant portion is at risk under the company&#146;s annual incentive plan, payable
primarily based on enterprise results, and to a lesser degree individual performance. We further detail each component of total direct compensation below. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:5%; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="justify"><B><I>Base Salary</I></B>.&nbsp;We review base salaries annually, but we do not necessarily award salary increases each year.
In determining base salary levels for executive officers, the committee considers the following qualitative and quantitative factors: job level and responsibilities, relevant experience, individual performance, recent corporate and business unit
performance, internal equity and our objective of paying competitive total direct compensation if performance is met. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">34 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:5%; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="justify">From time to time base salaries may be adjusted other than as a result of an
annual review in order to address competitive pressures or in connection with a promotion. Given the lower oil price environment in 2015, salaries for our NEOs and other senior executives were held flat at 2014 levels. </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">

</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:5%; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="justify"><B><I>Annual Incentive Plan (&#147;AIP&#148;)</I></B>.&nbsp;We establish an annual incentive
target for each executive officer based upon his or her position within the company, corresponding responsibilities and competitive annual incentive opportunity for similar positions in other companies. Payouts are in cash and may range from 0% to
200% of the target annual incentive opportunity based on actual enterprise and individual performance outcomes. Given the lower oil price environment in 2015, annual incentive targets for our NEOs and other senior executives were held flat from
2014. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:5%; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="justify"><B><I>2015 AIP Design</I></B>.&nbsp;The AIP payout for executive officers is
primarily determined based on enterprise performance results that align with the company&#146;s business strategy. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="68%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">

<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="12%"></TD>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:8pt"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff"><B><FONT COLOR="#ffffff">Weighting</FONT></B></FONT></TD></TR>


<TR STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="middle" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE="margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Production</P></TD>

<TD VALIGN="middle" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">25%</TD></TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#edf9d8" STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="middle" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE="margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Environment, Health &amp; Safety
(&#147;EHS&#148;)</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">20%</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="middle" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE="margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Capital and Exploratory Spend</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">20%</TD></TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#edf9d8" STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="middle" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE="margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Controllable Operated Cash Costs</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">20%</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="middle" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE="margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Cash Return on Capital Employed</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">10%</TD></TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#edf9d8" STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="middle" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE="margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Exploration Resource Additions</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1.50pt solid #000000">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1.50pt solid #000000">5%</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="middle" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE="margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Total</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">100%</TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:5%; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="justify">Payouts under the AIP depend on enterprise results, and payouts can range from 0% to 175% of
target. An individual performance multiplier can reduce the annual incentive payout down to zero or increase it by up to 25% of target based on actual individual performance results measured against pre-defined individual performance goals. There
will be no payout if the threshold level of enterprise performance is not achieved. The payout is capped at 200% of the target award. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:24pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><B>Illustration of 2015 AIP Design </B></P> <P STYLE="font-size:24pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt" ALIGN="center">


<IMG SRC="g96296g72y12.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
 </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:24pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:5%; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="justify"><B><I>Actual Cash Incentive Awards</I></B>.&nbsp;&nbsp;The following table shows actual
performance as a percent of target based on the 2015 results for each component of the AIP, and the actual cash incentive award for each NEO. As described below, although the formulaic calculation of the enterprise performance component of the AIP
should have paid out at 111% based on company performance during 2015, in light of the current commodity price environment, the committee exercised negative discretion to reduce the payout for the enterprise performance component to 85%. The
following discussion explains how the payouts for each component were determined. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD VALIGN="middle" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">Discretionary<BR> <P STYLE="margin-bottom:1pt; margin-top:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Committee<BR>Reduction</P></TD>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><B>&nbsp;</B></TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000" ALIGN="right"><B>85</B></TD>
<TD NOWRAP VALIGN="middle" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:8pt"><B>%&nbsp;</B></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:5%; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="justify"><B><I>Assessment of Individual Performance</I></B>.&nbsp;We assess individual performance based
on goals set at the beginning of each year, specific to each NEO. Following year end, achievement of these pre-defined individual goals is assessed. The CEO conducts performance reviews for the other NEOs and makes compensation recommendations to
the committee based on these reviews, with the committee making the final determination. The committee reviews the CEO&#146;s attainment of his individual performance objectives. This individual performance assessment for each NEO determines the
modifier used (if any) to influence the final payout of their annual incentive award. This review can also influence the grant date value of LTI compensation and base salary adjustments for the subsequent year. The target LTI value for any NEO can
be adjusted down to zero or increased by up to +25%, given the result of each individual performance assessment. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:5%; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="justify">In March
2015, the committee approved the individual objectives for our CEO and for other NEOs. None of the objectives had any specific weighting and are intended to be used together with other information the committee determines relevant to develop a
holistic evaluation of individual performance. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">37 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:5%; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="justify">In the first quarter of 2016, the committee evaluated 2015 performance for each
NEO against, among other factors, the approved individual objectives. For Mr.&nbsp;Hess, the committee reviewed and considered his 2015 performance self-assessment. For each of the other NEOs, the committee reviewed their respective 2015 performance
self-assessments, and considered Mr.&nbsp;Hess&#146; recommendation and summary of each of the other NEO&#146;s performance. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:5%; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="justify">Specific items considered by the committee in its assessment of individual performance are outlined below. After evaluating
Mr.&nbsp;Hess&#146; performance on these criteria, the committee concluded that his 2015 performance met expectations. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

addition, specific to each individual, the committee considered, among other things, the items listed below for each individual, as well as input from the CEO and other members of the board of directors. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:5%; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="justify">Mr.&nbsp;Hill delivered key business targets and major milestones set forth in his performance goals. He oversaw the successful
changes in the unconventional business strategy given the low commodity environment and oversaw significant advances in lean methodology throughout the company&#146;s operations, particularly in the Bakken. Mr.&nbsp;Hill also led various cost
reduction activities throughout the company and oversaw significant improvements in safety. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:5%; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="justify">Mr.&nbsp;Goodell delivered key
business targets as set forth in his performance goals. He oversaw the legal function&#146;s contributions to the successful sale of a 50% interest in our Bakken midstream assets and the preparation for the proposed initial public offering of Hess
Midstream Partners LP (the &#147;MLP&#148;). Additionally, in connection with the sale of the Hovensa assets and completion of its bankruptcy, Mr.&nbsp;Goodell successfully managed significant litigation issues to mitigate the impact on the company.
He also led a significant restructure of the legal organization, while strengthening talent capability and leadership succession. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">38 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:5%; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="justify">Mr.&nbsp;Rielly delivered key business targets as set forth in his performance
goals. He played a key role in executing our strategy to strengthen the company&#146;s balance sheet. He advanced the MLP&#146;s organizational capability and leadership in preparation for its proposed initial public offering. He also successfully
transitioned the financial services functions to Houston, while strengthening talent capability and leadership succession. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:5%; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="justify">Mr.&nbsp;Turner delivered key business targets as set forth in his performance goals. He successfully altered the
unconventional business strategy given the low commodity price environment, oversaw reductions in the Bakken and Utica drilling and completion costs, fostered functional excellence, and oversaw significant improvements in safety. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:5%; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="justify">After reviewing the 2015 pre-defined individual performance goals and considering the current low oil and gas price
environment, the committee determined to make no individual adjustment to annual incentive payments for any of the NEOs. The committee determined this action was appropriate despite the company having a strong performance year and each individual
meeting individual performance expectations. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:5%; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="justify"><B><I>LTI Program Structure.</I></B> Long-term Incentive (&#147;LTI&#148;)
compensation is an important tool to drive behavior that supports our business strategy. LTI compensation is also an important retention tool. As a result, LTI compensation represents the largest portion of each executive officer&#146;s target total
direct compensation package. For 2015 LTI awards, the performance-based component accounted for 80% of the total LTI award, based on grant date target value, which the committee believes supports alignment of the interests of our senior-most
management and stockholders. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1.50pt solid #21a32b; BORDER-BOTTOM:1.50pt solid #21a32b; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE="margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>Restricted&nbsp;Stock</B></P></TD>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1.50pt solid #21a32b; BORDER-BOTTOM:1.50pt solid #21a32b"><B>20%</B></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:5%; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="justify">For 2016, the committee considered stockholder feedback, the typical time horizons of
investment decisions for Hess&#146; business and industry, the current commodity price environment, the current performance metric for PSUs and market practice. During our stockholder outreach described above, we learned that an emphasis on
performance-based LTI is preferred and that investors supported the use of stock options as a component of performance-based LTI. The committee determined to approve certain changes to the long term incentive mix for Mr.&nbsp;Hess to eliminate
restricted stock and link 100% of Mr.&nbsp;Hess&#146; target LTI compensation to performance. For 2016, 70% of Mr.&nbsp;Hess&#146; target LTI award is in the form of PSUs and 30% is in the form of stock options. The committee determined to maintain
the long-term incentive mix for the company&#146;s other NEOs for 2016. For such NEOs, 80% of the target LTI compensation will be performance based, with 60% in the form of PSUs, 20% in the form of stock options and the remaining 20% in the form of
restricted stock. Payout of PSUs is contingent upon the company&#146;s TSR compared with that of our peer companies, identified below, over a three-year period. In addition, our TSR must be positive during the three-year performance period for
payout to exceed target, even if the company outperforms peers. Use of stock options, which remain exercisable for ten years, is supported by the </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">39 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="justify">
company&#146;s capital intensive industry, where the time horizon for investment decisions often extends over many years. Stock options, which only provide value upon absolute stock price
appreciation, also reinforce a balance between relative and absolute stock price performance goals, given PSU payout is primarily based on relative TSR. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="55%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:8pt" ALIGN="center">

<TD VALIGN="middle" ROWSPAN="2" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT STYLE="font-size:40pt">&#125;</FONT></P></TD>

<P STYLE="margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">100%&nbsp;performance-contingent</FONT></P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1.50pt solid #21a32b; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE="margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>Stock&nbsp;Options</B></P></TD>

<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:5%; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="justify"><B><I>Timing of LTI Awards.</I></B>&nbsp;In general, awards of restricted stock, stock options
and performance share units to the NEOs are made in early March after our financial statements have been audited by our independent public accountants. However, the committee retains discretion to vary the timing of awards as it deems appropriate.
</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:5%; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="justify"><B><I>Terms of LTI Awards.</I></B>&nbsp;Restricted stock awards generally fully vest three years from the date of grant,
and stock options vest ratably over a three-year period, generally subject to continued employment, and remain exercisable until ten&nbsp;years after the date of grant. PSUs, if earned, vest after the three-year performance period. We believe these
vesting periods promote retention and are consistent with market practices. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:5%; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="justify">Shares of restricted stock are issued and
outstanding from the date of grant, but are held in escrow until the vesting date. Restricted shares are therefore entitled to dividends if and when paid on shares of common stock. Dividends accrued on shares of restricted stock are paid upon
vesting. To the extent earned, performance share units will be paid in shares of Hess common stock which will vest and be issued following the end of the performance period. Dividend equivalents for PSUs will only be paid out on earned PSUs, after
the performance period. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:5%; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="justify"><B><I>Value of LTI Awards.</I></B>&nbsp;We aim to provide long-term awards such that together with
cash compensation, target total direct compensation is within a competitive range of market median. Compensation is intended to vary based on company and individual performance outcomes. The committee bases individual award levels on comparative
market data for the executive&#146;s position, award levels of comparably-situated executives, and an assessment of individual potential and performance. In making awards to any individual, the committee does not consider his or her gains made, or
failure to achieve gains, on prior restricted stock, stock option or performance share unit awards. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center">40 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:5%; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="justify">The charts below reflect the payout matrix for the outstanding PSU awards. In
defining the PSU payout schedules, the following guiding principles were used: for maximum payout, performance must be approximately top 15% for 2014 and 2015 awards, up from top quartile for 2013 awards; for target payout, performance must exceed
median; for threshold payout, approximately 25<SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">th</SUP>&nbsp;percentile must be achieved for any payout, and no payout is earned for performance below
25<SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">th</SUP> percentile. In addition, as described above, payout may not exceed target if our TSR during the performance measurement period is not positive. </P>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B><A NAME="tx96296_104"></A>Peer Group </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:5%; font-size:12pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="justify">The committee reviews compensation data from a comparative group of oil and gas companies to ensure our compensation and
benefit programs are competitive within our industry. For 2015, our peer group consisted of 13 companies, as shown below, with the additions of Continental and Pioneer, considering Hess&#146; relative size and business strategy. For 2016, our peer
group remained the same as 2015, with the exception of Talisman, which was acquired during 2015. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">
